With a final yank, and a yelp from Lulu, the little dog came skittering into the passageway behind Cody. He cringed and twisted the other way, waving the pole sickle menacingly in front of him, but nothing leaped out of the darkness at him. “Come along now,” he scolded the dog. “If I'm killed by something that goes bump in the night, where will you be?” He thought about that for a moment. “Other than very well fed, I mean.”
